FBIS4-52466 "dreas091_n_94005" FBIS-EAS-94-091 Daily Report 10 May 1994 Vietnam Denmark Clears Hanoi's 50 Million-Dollar Debt Denmark Clears Hanoi's 50 Million-Dollar Debt BK1005131294 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam in English 1000 GMT 10 May 94 BK1005131294 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam English BFN [Text] Denmark has cleared Vietnam of its 50.8 million-dollar debt. The Danish minister of cooperation, Mrs. Helle Aid, said the action was taken because Vietnam was a preferential counterpart of Denmark. Mrs. Helle Aid also announced that Denmark had cleared Cambodia of its debt because Cambodia was one of the poorest countries in the world and unable to repay its debt.
